reviews.text: Super slow service. Ordered a pork sandwich and have been waiting for more than 30 minutes when the man sitting next to me who came after I did already got his lunch rice set. Yet, when you enter the restaurant, they tell you that you have to give them back the table in 40 minutes. Honestly whenever I hear that I'd think: when do you start counting ? After you order or after your food actually arrives?

Food is good.  The hand craft beer from macau is just okay.  Staff is very attentive.  Maybe because there’re fewer mainland China people in this shopping mall today.  I really like the silence and peaceful HK.  What a lovely day!

Tried the lunch set. Reasonably priced. Staff was friendly and attentive. Roast pork was succulent but the skin is not very crispy. Portuguese egg tart was quite average, pastry is too heavy. Overall food quality is good. Will go again and try other dishes.
Reasonably priced and tasty Portuguese cuisine. Must try some of those tempting desserts next time.

Comparing to real Macau dishes, it sucks. We ordered pudding but they gave us a egg tart and refuse to change it. It’s crowded not because it is good but because of on Saturday or Sunday or in Festivals. NOT recommended.

result.formatted_address: 18 Sha Tin Centre St, Sha Tin, Hong Kong
result.name: New Town Plaza Phase 1

reviews.text:
The best shopping mall in Hong Kong:
1. itself + 6 more shopping malls, all inter-connected by enclosed air-conditioned walkways
2. Accessible by train, bus, minibuses, bicycles, private car (tons of parking space)
3. friendly affordable prices - not the Landmark or Pacific Place
It's easy to go around the place, convenient, but sometimes feel like the mall is kind of small.

It's the biggest mall in the region. Its been undergoing gentrification over the past few years. Local unique shops are being replaced by luxury chains. Car park is big but fills up quickly, and is expensive.
New Town Plaza Phase I is where you find the important shopping, City Super and lower level restaurant hall. There is direct access from the MTR Station and Shatin Park.
At Parkview : delicious food and good service👍

result.name: 沙田新城市廣場第一期

reviews.text: 商店按分類排列👍🏻
非常多內地客😥

成個商場嘅格局越嚟越似海港城，已經為自由行，而唔係再為沙田居民而設。
除非你真係好想買名牌，或者上食層食嘢，否則都係唔嚟好過！
小心俾自由行嘅巨型拖喼轆到隻腳， 成個商場比較行得舒服嘅係citysuper，起碼自由行唔會喺度買食材然後返屋企煮飯！

沙田市廣場比較少人等位的一家餐廳，食物品質可以，座位亦比較寬敞。

一直想去亞蘇爾嘅元朗店食澳門菜，但既然經過新城市廣場，就嚟呢間分店試吓。呢度地方唔算大，坐得比較迫，一到 12:30 pm 左右就坐滿人而且不斷有人喺店外排隊等位。話就話係澳門式嘅萄國菜，但叫咗嘅餸菜都有唔多唔小嘅港式 feel，例如非洲雞，雖然 1/4 隻份量唔多而且汁係熟悉嘅萄國雞汁，但勝在好嫩滑; 而鵝肝焗鴨飯，除咗有大大件嘅鵝肝之外，鴨肉飯有燉飯 feel，感覺唔錯。整體嚟講呢度啲食物嘅 CP值有番咁上下，服務方面亦算唔錯，可以有下次，唯一嘅敗筆就係新城市廣場嘅人流實在太旺，令呢度經常都咁多人，想安静一啲食餐飯都好難。

Tried the lunch set. Reasonably priced. Staff was friendly and attentive. Roast pork was succulent but the skin is not very crispy. Portuguese egg tart was quite average, pastry is too heavy. Overall food quality is good. Will go again and try other dishes.
